quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  4,163,"Verily, we have inspired thee as we inspired Noah and the prophets after him, and as we inspired Abraham, and Ishmael, and Jacob, and the tribes, and Jesus, and Job, and Jonas, and Aaron, and Solomon; and to David did we give Psalms"
  4,164,"Of apostles we have already told thee of some before; and of apostles some we have not told thee of;- But Moses did God speak to, speaking"
  4,165,"apostles giving glad tidings and warning, that men should have no argument against God, after the apostles, for God is mighty, wise"
  4,166,"But God bears witness to what He has revealed to thee: He revealed it in His knowledge, and the angels bear witness too; though God is witness enough"
  4,167,"Verily, those who misbelieve and obstruct the way of God, have erred a wide error"
  4,168,"Verily those who misbelieve and are unjust, God will not pardon them, nor will He guide them on the road"
  4,169,"save the road to hell, to dwell therein for aye;- that is easy enough to God"
  4,170,"O ye folk! the Apostle has come to you with truth from your Lord: believe then, for it is better for you. But if ye misbelieve, then God's is what is in the heavens and the earth, and God is knowing, wise"
  4,171,"O ye people of the Book! do not exceed in your religion, nor say against God aught save the truth. The Messiah, Jesus the son of Mary, is but the apostle of God and His Word, which He cast into Mary and a spirit from Him; believe then in God and His apostles, and say not 'Three.' Have done! it were better for you. God is only one God, celebrated be His praise that He should beget a Son! His is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth; and God sufficeth for a guardian"